Installed tools:
  java 21        jenkins LTS    nginx           cloudflared
  arkade  jq  yq  fx  task  just  fzf  btop  cfssl  ripgrep

Quick commands:
  jenkins-status   jenkins-logs    jenkins-restart    jenkins-start    jenkins-stop
  nginx-status     nginx-logs      nginx-reload

PRE-SETUP ACTIONS  (run these before or right after startup):

  1. Expose Jenkins publicly via Cloudflare Tunnel:
       one.dash.cloudflare.com → Networks → Connectors
       Create tunnel → Cloudflared → copy install command:
         sudo cloudflared service install <token>
       Add public hostname:
         Subdomain: jenkins   Domain: yourdomain.com
         Service:   HTTP      URL:    localhost:80
       Jenkins is now live at https://jenkins.yourdomain.com

  2. Install tools (Maven, Docker, Node.js, Trivy, AWS CLI, kubectl, Helm, Terraform, Ansible):
       sudo install-pipeline-tools

POST-SETUP ACTIONS  (run this AFTER Jenkins setup wizard):

  Complete Jenkins setup first:
    → Open it in browser  → Put initial admin password → Create admin username & password
    → Set its URL: Manage Jenkins → System → Jenkins URL → Save

  Then install Jenkins plugins (Git, SonarQube, Docker, Nexus, etc.):
    sudo install-plugins
